===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*tīuxan-'', from Indo-European ''*deuk-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[tian|tīan]], Old Saxon [[tiohan]] (Middle Dutch [[tien|tīen]]), Old High German [[ziohan]] (German [[ziehen]]), Old Norse [[toginn]], Gothic [[𐍄𐌹𐌿𐌷𐌰𐌽]]; and, from Indo-European, with Greek [[δεύκειν]], Latin [[ducere|dūcere]], Middle Welsh [[dygaf]].  Compare [[team#Old English|tēam]], [[teag|tēag]].

